  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "For my love ... - As a recompence for my love; or, this is the return which I get for all the expressions of my love to them. The enemies referred to were those whom he had treated kindly; to whom he had done good. This is not uncommon in the world. It was illustrated in an eminent degree in the life of the Saviour.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "But I give myself unto prayer - literally, \"I - prayer;\" that is, I am all prayer; I continually pray. This may mean, either, that he bore these trials with a meek spirit, and did not allow these things to disturb his devotions; or, more probably, that he prayed constantly \"for them;\" he desired their good, and sought it from above. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "But I give myself unto prayer - literally, \"I - prayer;\" that is, I am all prayer; I continually pray. This may mean, either, that he bore these trials with a meek spirit, and did not allow these things to disturb his devotions; or, more probably, that he prayed constantly \"for them;\" he desired their good, and sought it from above. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
